skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "21f1974e-54f1-4211-a23a-838535b275e7", "value": "\"Starting from 1903, Hong Kong had a list of Authorized Architects under the Public Health and Building Ordinance. The qualifications of an Authorized Architect were: 1) over 27 years of age, 2) has worked exclusively as a Civil Engineer or Architect for at least 8 years, dating from the commencement of his pupilage or professional training, 3) has had sufficient training and experience as a Civil Engineer or Architect. With regard to (2), any diploma especially to those issued by the Institute of Civil Engineers or the Royal Institute of British Architects.\"\n(100 Years Architects in Hong Kong, Tony LAM)"}
